#. <section class="sutta" id="sn24.96"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn24.96:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 24"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 24"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn24.96:0.2"
msgid "4. Catutthagamanavagga"
msgstr "4. The Fourth Round"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 96. Adukkhamasukhīsutta → adukkhamasukhīattāsuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn24.96:0.3"
msgid "96. Adukkhamasukhīsutta"
msgstr "96. The Self Is Neither Happy Nor Suffering"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn24.96:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn24.96:1.2"
msgid ""
"“Kismiṃ nu kho, bhikkhave, sati, kiṃ upādāya, kiṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi "
"uppajjati:"
msgstr ""
"“Mendicants, when what exists, because of grasping what and insisting on "
"what, does the view arise:"

msgctxt "sn24.96:1.3"
msgid "‘adukkhamasukhī attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā’”ti?"
msgstr "‘The self is neither happy nor suffering, and is sound after death’?”"

msgctxt "sn24.96:1.4"
msgid "“Bhagavaṃmūlakā no, bhante, dhammā … pe …."
msgstr "“Our teachings are rooted in the Buddha. …”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn24.96:2.1"
msgid ""
"“Rūpe kho, bhikkhave, sati, rūpaṃ upādāya, rūpaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi "
"uppajjati:"
msgstr ""
"“When form exists, because of grasping form and insisting on form, the view "
"arises:"

msgctxt "sn24.96:2.2"
msgid "‘adukkhamasukhī attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā’ti."
msgstr "‘The self is neither happy nor suffering, and is sound after death.’"

msgctxt "sn24.96:2.3"
msgid "Vedanāya sati …"
msgstr "When feeling …"

msgctxt "sn24.96:2.4"
msgid "saññāya sati …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn24.96:2.5"
msgid "saṅkhāresu sati …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn24.96:2.6"
msgid ""
"viññāṇe sati, viññāṇaṃ upādāya, viññāṇaṃ abhinivissa evaṃ diṭṭhi uppajjati:"
msgstr ""
"consciousness exists, because of grasping consciousness and insisting on "
"consciousness, the view arises:"

msgctxt "sn24.96:2.7"
msgid "‘adukkhamasukhī attā hoti arogo paraṃ maraṇā’ti."
msgstr "‘The self is neither happy nor suffering, and is sound after death.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.224"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn24.96:3.1"
msgid "Taṃ kiṃ maññatha, bhikkhave, "
msgstr "What do you think, mendicants? "

msgctxt "sn24.96:3.2"
msgid "rūpaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "Is form permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "sn24.96:3.3"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn24.96:3.4"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

msgctxt "sn24.96:3.5"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn24.96:3.6"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to "
"be regarded thus:"

msgctxt "sn24.96:3.7"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?"
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”"

msgctxt "sn24.96:3.8"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn24.96:3.9"
msgid "“Vedanā …"
msgstr "“Is feeling …"

msgctxt "sn24.96:3.10"
msgid "saññā …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn24.96:3.11"
msgid "saṅkhārā …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn24.96:3.12"
msgid "viññāṇaṃ niccaṃ vā aniccaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "consciousness permanent or impermanent?”"

msgctxt "sn24.96:3.13"
msgid "“Aniccaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Impermanent, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn24.96:3.14"
msgid "“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vā taṃ sukhaṃ vā”ti?"
msgstr "“But if it’s impermanent, is it suffering or happiness?”"

msgctxt "sn24.96:3.15"
msgid "“Dukkhaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“Suffering, sir.”"

msgctxt "sn24.96:3.16"
msgid ""
"“Yaṃ panāniccaṃ dukkhaṃ vipariṇāmadhammaṃ, kallaṃ nu taṃ samanupassituṃ:"
msgstr ""
"“But if it’s impermanent, suffering, and liable to fall apart, is it fit to "
"be regarded thus:"

msgctxt "sn24.96:3.17"
msgid "‘etaṃ mama, esohamasmi, eso me attā’”ti?"
msgstr "‘This is mine, I am this, this is my self’?”"

msgctxt "sn24.96:3.18"
msgid "“No hetaṃ, bhante”."
msgstr "“No, sir.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn24.96:4.1"
msgid ""
"“Tasmātiha, bhikkhave, yaṃ kiñci rūpaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā "
"bahiddhā vā oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā, "
"sabbaṃ rūpaṃ: ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ "
"sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"“So you should truly see any kind of form at all—past, future, or present; "
"internal or external; coarse or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: "
"<em>all</em> form—with right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not "
"this, this is not my self.’"

msgctxt "sn24.96:4.2"
msgid "Yā kāci vedanā …"
msgstr "You should truly see any kind of feeling …"

msgctxt "sn24.96:4.3"
msgid "yā kāci saññā …"
msgstr "perception …"

msgctxt "sn24.96:4.4"
msgid "ye keci saṅkhārā …"
msgstr "choices …"

msgctxt "sn24.96:4.5"
msgid ""
"yaṃ kiñci viññāṇaṃ atītānāgatapaccuppannaṃ ajjhattaṃ vā bahiddhā vā, "
"oḷārikaṃ vā sukhumaṃ vā hīnaṃ vā paṇītaṃ vā yaṃ dūre santike vā, sabbaṃ "
"viññāṇaṃ: ‘netaṃ mama, nesohamasmi, na meso attā’ti evametaṃ yathābhūtaṃ "
"sammappaññāya daṭṭhabbaṃ."
msgstr ""
"consciousness at all—past, future, or present; internal or external; coarse "
"or fine; inferior or superior; far or near: <em>all</em> consciousness—with "
"right understanding: ‘This is not mine, I am not this, this is not my self.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn24.96:5.1"
msgid ""
"Evaṃ passaṃ, bhikkhave, sutavā ariyasāvako rūpasmimpi nibbindati, vedanāyapi "
"nibbindati, saññāyapi nibbindati, saṅkhāresupi nibbindati, viññāṇasmimpi "
"nibbindati."
msgstr ""
"Seeing this, a learned noble disciple grows disillusioned with form, "
"feeling, perception, choices, and consciousness."

msgctxt "sn24.96:5.2"
msgid ""
"Nibbindaṃ virajjati; virāgā vimuccati. Vimuttasmiṃ vimuttamiti ñāṇaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"Being disillusioned, desire fades away. When desire fades away they’re "
"freed. When they’re freed, they know they’re freed."

msgctxt "sn24.96:5.3"
msgid ""
"‘Khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānātī”ti."
msgstr ""
"They understand: ‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been "
"completed, what had to be done has been done, there is no return to any "
"state of existence.’”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn24.96:5.4"
msgid "Catutthapeyyālo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn24.96:6.1"
msgid "Purimagamane aṭṭhārasa veyyākaraṇā,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn24.96:6.2"
msgid "Dutiyagamane chabbīsaṃ vitthāretabbāni;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn24.96:6.3"
msgid "Tatiyagamane chabbīsaṃ vitthāretabbāni,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn24.96:6.4"
msgid "Catutthagamane chabbīsaṃ vitthāretabbāni."
msgstr ""

#. </p></blockquote><p class="endsutta">
msgctxt "sn24.96:6.5"
msgid "Diṭṭhisaṃyuttaṃ samattaṃ."
msgstr "The Linked Discourses on views are complete."
